WEBVTT

00:01.269 --> 00:03.071
LATE FOR SCHOOL.
SEE YA.

00:03.904 --> 00:05.639
MAX, WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOUR EYE?

00:05.639 --> 00:07.875
HONEY?

00:07.875 --> 00:09.643
IS THAT MAKEUP?

00:11.679 --> 00:12.980
BULLIES WON'T PICK ON ME

00:12.980 --> 00:15.883
IF THEY THINK
I'VE ALREADY BEEN BEATEN UP.

00:15.883 --> 00:17.185
THEY LIKE FRESH MEAT.

00:19.320 --> 00:21.789
SOMEBODY'S PICKING ON YOU?
WHO, MAX? I WANT A NAME.

00:21.789 --> 00:26.794
HECTOR CLARK, BOBBY GARCIA,
DAVID CHIN, RICHIE GOODMAN,

00:26.794 --> 00:31.332
TIM SULLIVAN, PETER CISCO,
PRADI PITWANI.

00:33.601 --> 00:36.036
I KNOW IT'S TOUGHER
IN MIDDLE SCHOOL,

00:36.036 --> 00:38.972
BUT JUST TRY TO THINK
OF IT THIS WAY --

00:38.972 --> 00:40.741
BULLIES ARE JUST FRIENDS

00:40.741 --> 00:44.178
WHO DON'T REALIZE
HOW SPECIAL YOU ARE YET.

00:44.178 --> 00:47.381
WHAT KIND OF CRAP
ARE YOU TEACHING HIM?

00:48.916 --> 00:50.251
NO WONDER KIDS OF ALL RACES

00:50.251 --> 00:52.653
ARE COMING TOGETHER
TO BEAT UP ON MAX.

00:55.289 --> 00:58.659
OR AT LEAST DO BOTH EYES
AND ADD A LITTLE LIPSTICK.

00:58.659 --> 01:01.295
I CAN GUARANTEE THAT THERE
WILL BE A COUPLE OF BOYS

01:01.295 --> 01:03.697
WHO WILL WANT
TO BE YOUR FRIEND.

01:03.697 --> 01:07.601
MOM, THIS FAMILY HAS ONLY ROOM
FOR ONE GUY IN MAKEUP,

01:07.601 --> 01:10.738
AND THAT IS YOU.
GOOD DAY, SIR.

01:10.738 --> 01:12.406
I SAID, GOOD DAY, SIR!

01:14.508 --> 01:15.809
I JUST CAN'T UNDERSTAND

01:15.809 --> 01:17.911
WHY ANYONE WOULD WANT
TO PICK ON YOU.

01:17.911 --> 01:19.680
ARE YOU KIDDING?

01:19.680 --> 01:23.517
YOU'RE DRESSING HIM LIKE
HE'S STILL IN ELEMENTARY SCHOOL.

01:23.517 --> 01:26.254
DORKY SHIRT, DORKY PANTS...

01:27.321 --> 01:29.190
YOU CAN'T EVEN
SEE HIS BOXERS.

01:30.591 --> 01:33.361
WHY DON'T YOU JUST PUT HIM
IN A "TICKLE ME, ELMO" T-SHIRT

01:33.361 --> 01:35.463
AND SEND HIM TO HIS DEATH?

01:35.463 --> 01:37.931
I THINK HE LOOKS
REALLY CUTE.

01:37.931 --> 01:38.999
OKAY, DON'T LISTEN TO ME.

01:38.999 --> 01:40.368
HALEY?

01:40.368 --> 01:42.536
I GUESS THOSE SHOES
AREN'T TOO BAD...

01:42.536 --> 01:44.605
IF YOU'RE RUNNING AWAY
FROM SOMEONE.

01:44.605 --> 01:46.640
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

01:46.640 --> 01:48.609
I DIDN'T PICK
ANY OF THIS OUT!

01:48.609 --> 01:50.511
MAX, DO YOU WANT TO IGNORE
PEER PRESSURE

01:50.511 --> 01:51.845
AND BE JUDGED
FOR WHO YOU ARE,

01:51.845 --> 01:54.014
OR DO YOU JUST WANT
TO FOLLOW THE CROWD --

01:54.014 --> 01:55.583
FOLLOW THE CROWD!

01:56.984 --> 01:58.919
I NEED NEW CLOTHES, FAST.

01:58.919 --> 01:59.987
FINE,
WE'LL GO SHOPPING LATER.

01:59.987 --> 02:01.555
NO.

02:01.555 --> 02:04.892
SHE PICKS OUT MY CLOTHES NOW.
YOU HAD YOUR CHANCE.

02:07.428 --> 02:10.698
MAN, REMEMBER WHEN YOU USED
TO BE COOL, ANGIE?

02:10.698 --> 02:12.400
ANGIE IN HIGH SCHOOL.

02:12.400 --> 02:17.205
ANGIE WHEN WE GOT MARRIED.
ANGIE BECOMES A MOM!

02:18.472 --> 02:20.974
HEY, YOU'RE NOT SO COOL
ANYMORE, EITHER.

02:20.974 --> 02:22.210
REALLY?

02:22.210 --> 02:23.977
TALK TO THE BOXERS.
WA-CHA!

02:23.977 --> 02:26.714
'SUP, EH? 'SUP?

02:26.714 --> 02:29.717
'SUP, KITCHEN?
'SUP, TOAST?

02:29.717 --> 02:32.186
WHAT'S UP, OUTSIDE?
WA-CHA!

02:35.656 --> 02:37.558
NOW, TELL ME
WHICH OF THESE SETTINGS

02:37.558 --> 02:39.092
YOU LIKE FOR THE WEDDING.

02:39.092 --> 02:42.029
I'M JUST SO GLAD YOU CAME ACROSS
MY AD IN THE PHONE BOOK.

02:42.029 --> 02:45.466
I KNEW I'D GET BUSINESS IF I WAS
LISTED BEFORE TRIPLE-A EVENTS.

02:45.466 --> 02:48.436
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

02:48.436 --> 02:51.872
A-A-A-ANGIE'S WEDDINGS,
HOW CAN I HELP YOU?

02:56.143 --> 02:58.111
HEY, YOU'RE EARLY.

02:58.111 --> 02:59.580
COOL BRACELET.

02:59.580 --> 03:01.815
YEAH, WELL, TODD AND I HAVE
BEEN DATING FOR A WHILE,

03:01.815 --> 03:04.985
SO I FINALLY DECIDED
IT WAS TIME TO GO GREEN.

03:04.985 --> 03:06.820
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

03:06.820 --> 03:08.922
DIDN'T THEY DO THIS
AT YOUR OLD SCHOOL?

03:08.922 --> 03:11.058
EVERY COLOR BRACELET
IS SOMETHING DIFFERENT

03:11.058 --> 03:12.326
YOU'LL DO WITH A GUY.

03:12.326 --> 03:16.230
OH, YEAH.
YEAH, I'VE GONE GREEN.

03:16.230 --> 03:18.131
I EVEN WENT BLUE ONCE.

03:18.131 --> 03:21.402
WHAT?!
OH, MY GOD, BLUE?

03:24.405 --> 03:26.440
Didn't you get sand
everywhere?

03:29.243 --> 03:32.713
HEY, WHEN YOU'RE
IN THE MIDDLE OF BLUE,

03:32.713 --> 03:36.817
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHERE YOU ARE.

03:36.817 --> 03:38.852
MAN, WAIT TILL
EVERYBODY AT SCHOOL

03:38.852 --> 03:40.788
FINDS OUT THAT
YOU'VE DONE BLUE.

03:40.788 --> 03:42.856
THEY'RE GONNA THINK
I'M, LIKE, A SLUT, ARE THEY?

03:42.856 --> 03:44.191
ARE YOU KIDDING?

03:44.191 --> 03:45.859
EVERYONE'S GONNA THINK
YOU'RE COOL.

03:45.859 --> 03:49.597
AT ST. THERESA'S, YOU'RE ONLY
A SLUT IF YOU GET PREGNANT.

03:54.201 --> 03:56.003
HEY, DAD,
WHERE'S OUR BIBLE?

03:56.003 --> 03:58.238
I'VE GOT HOMEWORK
FOR MY RELIGIOUS STUDIES CLASS.

03:58.238 --> 03:59.573
CHECK THE LIVING ROOM.

03:59.573 --> 04:01.141
WHEN YOUR GRANDMA PASSED OUT
LAST NIGHT,

04:01.141 --> 04:04.011
I TOUCHED IT TO HER HEAD TO SEE
IF IT'D LEAVE A BURN MARK.

04:06.714 --> 04:08.516
HI, HALEY.

04:08.516 --> 04:11.719
OH, CUTE BRACELET!

04:11.719 --> 04:14.221
YOU KNOW, A BLUE ONE
WOULD MAKE A GREAT GIFT

04:14.221 --> 04:15.222
FOR THE FLOWER GIRL.

04:15.222 --> 04:17.524
DO NOT...DO THAT.

04:21.829 --> 04:26.033
HEY, THERE'S THAT KID FROM
THE COVER OF COOL GUY MONTHLY!

04:33.140 --> 04:35.543
OH, HEY, I SAW THIS MOVIE.

04:35.543 --> 04:37.978
"NERDS, NERDS, NERDS, NERDS!"

04:40.013 --> 04:41.349
WHAT'S GOING ON?

04:41.349 --> 04:45.118
[ Panting ]
CLOTHES...DIDN'T WORK.

04:45.118 --> 04:46.887
WHO ARE YOUR FRIENDS?

04:46.887 --> 04:48.589
NOT...MY FRIENDS.

04:48.589 --> 04:50.958
WE WERE JUST RUNNING
IN THE SAME DIRECTION...

04:50.958 --> 04:53.361
AWAY FROM BULLIES.

04:53.361 --> 04:55.996
YOU WERE CHASED AGAIN?
THAT'S HORRIBLE.

04:55.996 --> 04:57.030
I KNOW.

04:57.030 --> 04:58.766
THANK GOD THAT FAT KID
HAD TO STOP

04:58.766 --> 05:00.300
TO TAKE A HIT
OFF HIS INHALER.

05:00.300 --> 05:02.736
THEY WOULD'VE
GRABBED US ALL.

05:02.736 --> 05:05.072
WHERE'S THE FRONT DOOR?

05:05.072 --> 05:06.239
THERE.

05:06.239 --> 05:09.577
AFTER ME, FELLAS,
COME ON!

05:09.577 --> 05:11.545
I'LL BE UP IN MY ROOM.

05:16.617 --> 05:17.851
ANGIE, THIS IS SERIOUS.

05:17.851 --> 05:19.687
IF MAX DOESN'T MAKE
FRIENDS SOON,

05:19.687 --> 05:22.656
HE'S GONNA BE BRANDED A LOSER
FOR THE REST OF MIDDLE SCHOOL.

05:22.656 --> 05:24.825
SO, WHAT'S HE SUPPOSED
TO DO?

05:24.825 --> 05:29.296
I DON'T KNOW.
I MEAN, I GOT LUCKY.

05:29.296 --> 05:31.665
I STARTED DATING
SOME HOT CHEERLEADER.

05:31.665 --> 05:34.001
USED TO TAKE HER TO ALL
THE PARTIES AND SAY,

05:34.001 --> 05:35.202
"LOOK AT WHAT GEORGE GOT!

05:35.202 --> 05:36.937
WA-CHA!"

05:39.373 --> 05:41.975
[ Panting ] WHICH WAY?
WHICH WAY?

05:41.975 --> 05:43.477
TH-THROUGH THERE.

05:45.245 --> 05:47.047
THE FRUIT IN THE BOWL IS FAKE!

05:47.047 --> 05:49.783
WHAT AM I SAYING? THAT KID'S
NOT GOING FOR THE FRUIT.

05:51.084 --> 05:53.554
WHY DIDN'T I THINK
OF THIS EARLIER?

05:53.554 --> 05:55.923
DINA'S SON, KYLE, GOES
TO THE SAME SCHOOL AS MAX.

05:55.923 --> 05:57.591
THEY SHOULD GET TO KNOW
EACH OTHER.

05:57.591 --> 05:59.326
MAX, GET DOWN HERE!

05:59.326 --> 06:01.128
NO, ANGIE,
KIDS DON'T MAKE FRIENDS

06:01.128 --> 06:03.764
BY HAVING THEIR MOMMIES
SET THEM UP ON BLIND DATES.

06:03.764 --> 06:05.766
LOOK, A KID TRIPS
IN THE CAFETERIA.

06:05.766 --> 06:08.335
YOU LAUGH SO HARD THAT MILK
COMES OUT OF YOUR NOSE.

06:08.335 --> 06:11.439
THE KID NEXT TO YOU IS LAUGHING
SO HARD HE ACCIDENTALLY FARTS.

06:11.439 --> 06:13.306
BRRRP!

06:13.306 --> 06:15.643
BOOM! FRIENDS FOR LIFE!

06:18.946 --> 06:21.515
DO YOU KNOW KYLE
FROM SCHOOL?

06:21.515 --> 06:24.518
I-I'VE SEEN HIM AROUND.
WHY?

06:24.518 --> 06:26.654
WELL, MAYBE HE'D LIKE
TO GO TO THE MOVIES

06:26.654 --> 06:27.921
WITH YOU THIS WEEKEND.

06:27.921 --> 06:30.123
MOM, NO!
TRUST ME, IT'LL BE FUN.

06:30.123 --> 06:32.359
KYLE, WOULD YOU LIKE
TO GO TO THE MOVIES

06:32.359 --> 06:33.761
WITH MAX THIS WEEKEND?

06:36.329 --> 06:37.898
NO, NO, NO!

06:37.898 --> 06:40.033
HE'S A LOSER,
LOSER, LOSER!

06:40.033 --> 06:41.168
NO WAY!

06:41.168 --> 06:43.270
I'M NOT GOING TO HANG OUT
WITH HIM!

06:43.270 --> 06:46.073
EVERYONE KNOWS
HE'S A LOSER.

06:46.073 --> 06:49.943
HEY! YOU'RE IN MY BACKYARD WITH
YOUR MOMMY LOOKING AT CHINA,

06:49.943 --> 06:52.412
SO WHO'S THE REAL LOSER,
HUH, PRINCESS?!

06:54.482 --> 06:56.684
ANGIE, DINA, HOW ARE YOU?

07:00.187 --> 07:02.022
LET'S GO, SON.

07:04.558 --> 07:07.094
[ INTRO TO WAR'S "LOW RIDER"
PLAYS ]

07:10.898 --> 07:16.203
* ALL MY FRIENDS
KNOW THE LOW RIDER *

07:17.638 --> 07:22.242
* THE LOW RIDER
IS A LITTLE HIGHER *

07:39.760 --> 07:42.630
DAD, DO I HAVE
TO DO THIS?

07:42.630 --> 07:44.431
COME ON,
YOU LOVE SKATING, MAX.

07:44.431 --> 07:47.467
NOW, GET OUT THERE.
YOU MIGHT MAKE SOME FRIENDS.

07:47.467 --> 07:49.770
THIS IS STUPID.

07:55.976 --> 07:59.146
MAN, IT'S HARD
WHEN YOU DON'T FIT IN.

07:59.146 --> 08:02.049
[ Laughing ]
REMEMBER WHEN WE WERE TRYING

08:02.049 --> 08:03.684
TO GET INTO THE ROLLER
DISCO CROWD,

08:03.684 --> 08:05.352
AND YOU WERE
SPINNING ME AROUND

08:05.352 --> 08:08.355
'CAUSE YOU WERE GONNA WHIP ME
OUT SO I'D LOOK REALLY COOL?

08:08.355 --> 08:09.489
BUT THEN I GOT SCARED,

08:09.489 --> 08:10.891
AND I KEPT HOLDING ON
TO YOUR HANDS,

08:10.891 --> 08:13.126
AND WE JUST KEPT GOING ROUND
AND ROUND IN CIRCLES,

08:13.126 --> 08:15.428
LIKE WE WERE DANCING,
REMEMBER?

08:15.428 --> 08:18.298
[ LAUGHING ]

08:18.298 --> 08:21.234
I THINK YOU HIT YOUR HEAD, MAN,
'CAUSE I WASN'T THERE.

08:21.234 --> 08:22.770
NO, I SPECIFICALLY REMEM--

08:22.770 --> 08:24.705
THAT WASN'T ME.

08:26.640 --> 08:29.509
MAX, THAT WAS AWESOME!

08:29.509 --> 08:31.579
WAY TO GO, LITTLE BUDDY.

08:31.579 --> 08:33.746
[ Sarcastically ] YEAH,
WAY TO GO, LITTLE BUDDY.

08:33.746 --> 08:37.017
[ BOYS LAUGHING ]

08:37.017 --> 08:38.251
I'M SORRY.

08:38.251 --> 08:40.386
Look, if you want to be cool
with these guys,

08:40.386 --> 08:42.155
this one time, all right,

08:42.155 --> 08:43.890
I give you permission
to tell me off.

08:43.890 --> 08:45.959
Say something like,
"Get out of here, old man."

08:45.959 --> 08:47.494
GET OUT OF HERE,
FAT HEAD!

08:47.494 --> 08:48.862
I'VE HAD ENOUGH
OF YOUR CRAP!

08:50.698 --> 08:53.233
YEAH, LIKE THAT.
OKAY, THAT'S GOOD.

08:53.233 --> 08:54.702
I'LL BE BACK IN AN HOUR.

08:54.702 --> 08:56.637
YOU COME BACK WHEN I TELL YOU
TO COME BACK!

08:56.637 --> 08:58.639
WHY DON'T YOU GO HOME
IN THE MINIVAN

08:58.639 --> 09:00.741
AND START MY DINNER,
SOCCER MOM?!

09:02.576 --> 09:03.744
I love you, Dad.

09:10.584 --> 09:12.886
GEORGE,
CHECK OUT THESE BRACELETS.

09:12.886 --> 09:15.022
I SAW CARMEN'S FRIEND
WEARING ONE.

09:15.022 --> 09:18.859
THEY'RE SO CUTE!
I GOT ONE IN EVERY COLOR.

09:20.527 --> 09:22.095
IT WAS SO SAD.

09:22.095 --> 09:24.531
THE BOY AT THE STORE
HAD SOME KIND OF DISORDER.

09:24.531 --> 09:29.302
WHEN HE GAVE ME MY CHANGE,
HE WAS JUST [PANTING] SHAKING.

09:29.302 --> 09:34.507
WELL, WHILE YOU WERE OUT
GETTING "BRACELETS"...

09:34.507 --> 09:36.209
[ CHATTERING ]

09:36.209 --> 09:38.578
I WENT OUT AND GOT MAX
SOME FRIENDS.

09:38.578 --> 09:40.213
HONEY, THAT'S GREAT.

09:40.213 --> 09:42.850
AND THOSE FRIENDS,
THE ONES THAT I GOT HIM

09:42.850 --> 09:45.052
WHEN I TOOK HIM
TO THE SKATE PARK,

09:45.052 --> 09:48.021
ARE COMING OVER FOR SOME BURGERS
THAT I'M MAKING.

09:48.021 --> 09:51.792
THERE'S NO REASON TO TALK LIKE
THIS ANYMORE, BUT I LIKE IT!

09:58.331 --> 10:00.533
WANT TO SEE
THE COOLEST THING EVER?

10:00.533 --> 10:01.835
WA-CHA!

10:03.536 --> 10:06.273
GEORGE,
DID YOU KNOW ABOUT THIS?

10:06.273 --> 10:08.942
I...DID NOT.

10:08.942 --> 10:11.912
ALL THE GUYS
THINK IT'S REALLY COOL.

10:11.912 --> 10:14.314
WHICH GENIUS
TALKED YOU INTO THAT?

10:14.314 --> 10:15.816
BODIE.

10:15.816 --> 10:19.787
LET ME GUESS --
BODIE'S WEARING THE TRASH CAN?

10:20.921 --> 10:23.924
OKAY, GUYS.
COME ON, THAT'S ENOUGH.

10:23.924 --> 10:26.526
WHOA, WHY ARE YOU WEARING
ALL THOSE BRACELETS?

10:26.526 --> 10:28.461
YOU'RE A MOM.

10:28.461 --> 10:33.667
JUST BECAUSE I'M A MOM DOESN'T
MEAN I CAN'T HAVE A LITTLE FUN.

10:33.667 --> 10:37.771
OH, DUDE,
YOU ARE SO PIMPIN'.

10:37.771 --> 10:39.206
DARYL HANNAH?

10:40.774 --> 10:43.043
Boy: GO, MAX!

10:43.043 --> 10:46.279
MAX, NO! THIS WAS NOT
ON THE SAFETY VIDEO WE WATCHED.

10:46.279 --> 10:48.248
ANGIE, RELAX, IT'S OKAY.

10:48.248 --> 10:49.616
NO, IT'S NOT.

10:49.616 --> 10:51.651
REMEMBER, SAMMY THE SKATER,

10:51.651 --> 10:53.153
THE PENGUIN
WITH THE LITTLE HELMET?

10:53.153 --> 10:55.555
* YOU CAN BE SAFE
AND STILL BE RAD *

10:55.555 --> 10:59.092
* WHEN YOU WEAR YOUR HELMET
AND YOUR ELBOW PADS *

11:00.961 --> 11:02.095
OHH...

11:02.095 --> 11:05.498
YOU KNOW WHAT ELSE SAMMY
THE SKATER SINGS, ANGIE?

11:05.498 --> 11:07.768
* SHUT UP, SHUT UP,
YOU'RE MAKING IT WORSE *

11:07.768 --> 11:09.803
* NOW MEET ME
IN THE KITCHEN *

11:11.905 --> 11:13.306
ANGIE, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

11:13.306 --> 11:15.308
YOU'RE EMBARRASSING HIM
IN FRONT OF HIS FRIENDS.

11:15.308 --> 11:17.878
THOSE AREN'T THE KIND OF FRIENDS
I WANT MAX TO HAVE.

11:17.878 --> 11:19.813
THEY'RE OLDER,
THEY'RE RECKLESS.

11:19.813 --> 11:21.181
LOOK, HE ALREADY CHANGED
HIS HAIR.

11:21.181 --> 11:22.816
HE'S TOO DESPERATE
FOR FRIENDS.

11:22.816 --> 11:25.886
WHAT OTHER STUPID THINGS IS HE
GONNA DO TO TRY TO IMPRESS THEM?

11:25.886 --> 11:27.755
LOOK,
THEY'RE JUST BEING GUYS.

11:27.755 --> 11:30.891
WHEN WE GET TOGETHER,
WE DO CRAZY STUFF.

11:30.891 --> 11:32.893
CAN YOU IMAGINE
YOU AND YOUR GIRLFRIENDS

11:32.893 --> 11:34.294
GOING TO A RAIDERS GAME

11:34.294 --> 11:36.764
AND PAINTING YOUR CHESTS
SILVER AND BLACK?

11:36.764 --> 11:38.198
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:40.700 --> 11:43.103
GEORGE!

11:43.103 --> 11:45.205
JUST BE HAPPY
HE HAS FRIENDS, OKAY?

11:45.205 --> 11:47.707
YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO BE A LONER.

11:47.707 --> 11:52.312
BODIE, BODIE,
BODIE, BODIE!

11:56.316 --> 11:58.218
[ CRASHING ]

11:59.920 --> 12:03.857
THAT STILL HURTS A LOT LESS
THAN BEING ALONE.

12:03.857 --> 12:05.692
RIGHT, BODIE?

12:05.692 --> 12:08.896
COME ON, MAN, GET UP.
I'M TRYING TO MAKE A POINT HERE.

12:08.896 --> 12:11.398
IF HE'S IN THAT MUCH PAIN,
ANGIE,

12:11.398 --> 12:13.934
AT LEAST WE KNOW
HE'S NOT ON DRUGS.

12:20.273 --> 12:21.909
[ Laughing ] HE GOES DOWN
THE TABLE, UP THE RAMP, MOM,

12:22.876 --> 12:26.213
OVER THE GRILL,
AND INTO THE KITCHEN!

12:26.213 --> 12:29.382
THAT'S WHY I THINK WE NEED
A WOMAN PRESIDENT.

12:29.382 --> 12:30.350
HEY, HONEY.

12:34.654 --> 12:37.124
NO, ANGIE, ANGIE,
DON'T END IT.

12:37.124 --> 12:40.360
IT'S JUST ONE GRAY HAIR.
WE'LL DYE IT.

12:40.360 --> 12:41.661
WHAT'S GOING ON?

12:41.661 --> 12:44.597
I HAD AN INTERESTING LITTLE TRIP
TO THE GROCERY STORE.

12:44.597 --> 12:46.033
ANOTHER SHOPPING STORY.

12:46.033 --> 12:48.368
LET ME HAVE THOSE SCISSORS.

12:48.368 --> 12:52.005
WHEN THE TEENAGE BOY BAGGING MY
GROCERIES NOTICED MY BRACELETS,

12:52.005 --> 12:53.306
I TOOK IT AS A COMPLIMENT.

12:53.306 --> 12:54.908
WHEN HE HELPED ME TO THE CAR,

12:54.908 --> 12:56.376
I THOUGHT,
"THAT WAS REALLY SWEET."

12:56.376 --> 12:58.245
WHEN HE PUT HIS HAND
ON MY BUTT

12:58.245 --> 13:00.680
AND TOLD ME THAT HE'D NEVER DONE
PURPLE WITH AN OLDER CHICK,

13:00.680 --> 13:02.149
I HIT HIM.

13:02.149 --> 13:05.285
WHEN HE STOPPED CRYING,
AND WE FOUND HIS RETAINER,

13:05.285 --> 13:07.454
HE TOLD ME THAT EACH
OF THOSE COLORS

13:07.454 --> 13:10.991
STANDS FOR SOMETHING DIFFERENT
YOU'LL DO WITH A BOY.

13:12.993 --> 13:14.794
DID YOU HAVE TO
CUT THEM ALL OFF?

13:16.396 --> 13:19.867
CARMEN WAS WEARING A BUNCH
OF THOSE BRACELETS YESTERDAY.

13:19.867 --> 13:22.535
CARMEN, GET DOWN HERE!

13:22.535 --> 13:26.874
IN MY DAY YOU DIDN'T GO AROUND
ADVERTISING THIS STUFF.

13:26.874 --> 13:28.275
YOU'D GO OFF WITH A GUY,

13:28.275 --> 13:30.777
AND THEN IF HE WENT TOO FAR
YOU SLAPPED HIM.

13:30.777 --> 13:34.181
NOW, IF SLAPPING WAS YOUR THING,
IT GOT A LITTLE CONFUSING.

13:34.181 --> 13:35.282
MOM!

13:35.282 --> 13:38.919
ANOTHER SOURCE OF CONFUSION --
BITING.

13:40.888 --> 13:42.489
LET ME SEE YOUR WRIST.

13:43.823 --> 13:45.258
ORANGE,

13:45.258 --> 13:47.727
BLUE, GREEN, PURPLE,
RED, BLACK, PINK,

13:47.727 --> 13:50.630
ANOTHER WEIRDER KIND OF BLUE.
WHAT WOULD YOU CALL THAT?

13:50.630 --> 13:51.664
TEAL.
TEAL!

13:51.664 --> 13:54.367
CARMEN, YOU'RE TEAL-ING?

13:56.103 --> 13:58.038
YOU'RE A TEAL-ER?

13:59.439 --> 14:02.442
WE KNOW ABOUT THE BRACELETS.
WE NEED TO HAVE A SERIOUS TALK.

14:02.442 --> 14:04.644
NO, WE DON'T.
EVERYONE JUST CALM DOWN.

14:04.644 --> 14:06.513
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

14:06.513 --> 14:08.381
THEN WHY ARE YOU WEARING
THE BRACELETS?

14:08.381 --> 14:10.083
BECAUSE PEOPLE
THINK IT'S COOL.

14:10.083 --> 14:12.485
A WEEK AGO HARDLY ANYONE
AT SCHOOL TALKED TO ME.

14:12.485 --> 14:14.421
NOW EVERYONE LIKES ME.

14:14.421 --> 14:17.290
YOU LEFT PUBLIC SCHOOL BECAUSE
EVERYONE THOUGHT YOU WERE EASY.

14:17.290 --> 14:19.726
NOW YOU WANT EVERYONE
TO THINK YOU'RE EASY?

14:19.726 --> 14:24.431
BECAUSE I'M MATURING.

14:26.934 --> 14:29.869
UM, WARD, JUNE?

14:31.404 --> 14:35.342
I HATE TO INTERRUPT ONE PARENTAL
FAILURE WITH ANOTHER,

14:35.342 --> 14:37.911
BUT THE BEAV'S BEEN ARRESTED
AT THE MALL.

14:37.911 --> 14:39.646
George: WHAT? FOR WHAT?

14:39.646 --> 14:40.948
THEY WOULDN'T TELL ME.

14:40.948 --> 14:42.549
HE GOT IN TROUBLE
WITH THOSE SKATER PUNKS.

14:42.549 --> 14:44.384
THEY'RE HOLDING HIM
DOWN THERE.

14:44.384 --> 14:46.486
I'LL HANDLE THIS.

14:46.486 --> 14:48.621
I TOLD YOU HE WAS GONNA
DO SOMETHING STUPID

14:48.621 --> 14:49.756
WITH THOSE BOYS.

14:49.756 --> 14:52.259
DON'T WORRY.

14:52.259 --> 14:54.962
NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENED
AT THE MALL,

14:54.962 --> 14:58.298
HE WILL HAVE HIS DAY
IN FOOD COURT.

14:58.298 --> 14:59.399
[ LAUGHS ]

14:59.399 --> 15:01.868
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY.
COME ON, COME ON.

15:01.868 --> 15:06.439
IF WE DON'T LAUGH,
WE'LL CRY.

15:07.640 --> 15:09.376
[ LAUGHS ]

15:19.819 --> 15:21.388
IS ANYBODY HERE?!

15:21.388 --> 15:24.091
HE'LL BE BACK IN A SECOND.
HE'S CHECKING ON MY KID.

15:24.091 --> 15:26.026
YOU KNOW,
THIS IS A WASTE OF TIME, MAN.

15:26.026 --> 15:27.527
SKATEBOARDING'S NOT A CRIME.

15:27.527 --> 15:29.262
SO A KID, LIKE,
GRINDS ON A RAIL

15:29.262 --> 15:30.863
OR TRIES TO JUMP
A FOUNTAIN.

15:30.863 --> 15:34.167
IT'S LIKE THESE MALL COPS
GOT NOTHING BETTER TO DO.

15:34.167 --> 15:35.535
MY SON STABBED
ANOTHER GANGBANGER

15:35.535 --> 15:37.237
AND THREW HIM
DOWN THE ESCALATOR.

15:39.606 --> 15:41.808
SO, YOU THINK THEY'RE KEEPING
BOTH OF OUR KIDS

15:41.808 --> 15:43.376
IN THE SAME ROOM
BACK THERE?

15:43.376 --> 15:44.311
PROBABLY.

15:44.311 --> 15:46.813
MAX, ARE YOU OKAY?!

15:46.813 --> 15:49.116
MAX, IF YOU CAN HEAR ME, SON,

15:49.116 --> 15:51.251
DON'T HURT ANY
OF THOSE OTHER BOYS.

15:51.251 --> 15:54.021
YOU CAN'T AFFORD
YOUR THIRD STRIKE!

15:56.523 --> 15:57.724
MAX, ARE YOU OKAY?

15:57.724 --> 15:58.758
YEAH, I'M FINE.

15:58.758 --> 16:00.127
I NEED YOU TO SIGN THIS.

16:00.127 --> 16:02.062
YOUR KID'S NOT ALLOWED
BACK IN THE MALL.

16:02.062 --> 16:04.097
WE'RE GONNA HAVE HIS PICTURE
ON FILE.

16:04.097 --> 16:05.232
WHOA, MAN,
THAT'S A LITTLE HARSH.

16:05.232 --> 16:06.266
THEY WERE JUST
SKATEBOARDING.

16:06.266 --> 16:08.035
HE WASN'T SKATEBOARDING.

16:08.035 --> 16:11.138
I JUST FINISHED GRABBING THIS
GUY'S KID OUT OF A KNIFE FIGHT,

16:11.138 --> 16:13.706
AND THEN I FIND YOUR SON
AND SIX OF HIS FRIENDS

16:13.706 --> 16:14.874
BEATING UP ANOTHER KID.

16:14.874 --> 16:16.376
MAX, IS THIS TRUE?

16:20.880 --> 16:22.549
DON'T BE TOO HARD
ON YOURSELF.

16:22.549 --> 16:25.185
ONCE A KID GOES DOWN THAT ROAD,
THERE AIN'T MUCH YOU CAN DO.

16:25.185 --> 16:27.120
WELL, MY KID'S NOT GOING
DOWN THAT ROAD, OKAY?

16:27.120 --> 16:28.221
HE'S SMARTER THAN THAT.

16:28.221 --> 16:30.523
TURN TO YOUR RIGHT.

16:37.064 --> 16:39.366
HE'S DYSLEXIC, MAN,
JUST TURN HIM.

16:48.007 --> 16:49.909
GEORGE, TAKE IT EASY.

16:49.909 --> 16:52.345
MAX,
WHY WOULD YOU DO THIS?

16:52.345 --> 16:54.481
THIS GUY AT THE MALL
CALLED TREVOR A NAME.

16:54.481 --> 16:56.916
SO, THAT GIVES YOU THE RIGHT
TO GANG UP ON THE BOY?

16:56.916 --> 17:00.220
I HAD TO STAND UP FOR HIM.
HE'D DO THE SAME THING FOR ME.

17:00.220 --> 17:02.122
YOU MESS WITH ONE OF US,
YOU MESS WITH ALL OF US.

17:02.122 --> 17:04.191
THAT'S IT!
COME HERE.

17:04.191 --> 17:06.159
STAND RIGHT THERE.

17:06.159 --> 17:07.460
COVER YOUR EYES.

17:09.028 --> 17:10.430
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

17:10.430 --> 17:13.031
LOOK, THOSE KIDS ARE GONNA
END UP IN PRISON.

17:13.031 --> 17:14.934
I KNOW BECAUSE I GREW UP
WITH KIDS LIKE THAT.

17:14.934 --> 17:17.569
AND I DIDN'T WORK MY ASS OFF
TO LET THAT HAPPEN TO YOU.

17:17.569 --> 17:19.839
MAX, GO UPSTAIRS
AND WASH THAT OUT YOURSELF.

17:19.839 --> 17:21.473
THEN WAIT IN YOUR ROOM.

17:23.041 --> 17:25.044
DID YOU HEAR HIM?

17:25.044 --> 17:27.079
WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON
WITH OUR KIDS?

17:27.079 --> 17:28.515
I DON'T KNOW.

17:30.750 --> 17:31.884
ARE WE BAD PARENTS?

17:31.884 --> 17:33.253
NO!

17:33.253 --> 17:35.488
YOU'VE BEEN TOUGH,
I'VE BEEN FORGIVING.

17:35.488 --> 17:39.025
WE'VE GONE INTO HUGE DEBT TO GET
CARMEN INTO THE RIGHT SCHOOL.

17:39.025 --> 17:40.660
WE'VE BEEN UP HALF THE NIGHT
WITH MAX,

17:40.660 --> 17:42.895
HELPING HIM WITH
HIS LEARNING DISABILITIES.

17:42.895 --> 17:45.031
WE'VE ALWAYS PUT THEM FIRST.

17:45.031 --> 17:46.466
WELL, IT'S NOT ENOUGH

17:46.466 --> 17:49.302
'CAUSE THEY KEEP FALLING IN
WITH THE WRONG PEOPLE.

17:49.302 --> 17:51.938
LAST YEAR
MAX WAITED UP FOR SANTA.

17:51.938 --> 17:54.307
THIS YEAR HE AND HIS CREW
ARE GONNA WAIT ON THE ROOF

17:54.307 --> 17:57.210
AND JACK HIS SLEIGH.

17:57.210 --> 18:00.313
GOD KNOWS WHAT CARMEN'S
GONNA DO WITH THE ELVES.

18:05.152 --> 18:07.220
WE TALKED ABOUT THIS BEFORE.

18:07.220 --> 18:09.756
MAYBE IT'S THE CITY.

18:09.756 --> 18:12.259
MAYBE THERE'S A BETTER PLACE
TO RAISE KIDS.

18:12.259 --> 18:14.761
GEORGE, I'M NOT MOVING
OUT OF THE CITY.

18:14.761 --> 18:17.397
HEY, YOU GUYS,
THERE'S A HIGH-SPEED CHASE

18:17.397 --> 18:19.098
ABOUT TO GO PAST THE HOUSE.

18:19.098 --> 18:21.268
COME ON, LET'S GO CHEER ON
THE CARJACKER.

18:21.268 --> 18:24.304
[ SIREN WAILING ]

18:24.304 --> 18:25.638
I'LL MISS YOUR MOM.

18:25.638 --> 18:28.141
LET'S GET THE HELL
OUT OF THE CITY.

18:30.177 --> 18:31.678
YOU KNOW, ANGIE,
IF WE LEAVE L.A.,

18:31.678 --> 18:34.414
THIS WILL BE THE LAST CAR CHASE
WE EVER SEE.

18:34.414 --> 18:36.949
YOU GET A BOTTLE OF WINE.
I'LL GET THE CHAIRS.

18:36.949 --> 18:38.285
GO, GO, GO, GO!

18:40.320 --> 18:42.355
MOM, SAVE ME A SPOT!

18:48.995 --> 18:51.097
HEY, GEORGE, CHECK IT OUT!

18:51.097 --> 18:52.599
I FOUND MY OLD SKATES.

18:52.599 --> 18:53.733
[ LAUGHING ]

18:56.269 --> 18:59.439
HEY, HEY, HEY,
REMEMBER THIS?

19:02.509 --> 19:05.212
LOOK, I'M TELLING YOU
FOR THE LAST TIME, BERNIE,

19:05.212 --> 19:06.246
THAT WASN'T ME!

19:06.246 --> 19:07.880
OH, YEAH?

19:09.849 --> 19:15.488
WELL, THEN WHOSE SKATES
ARE THESE, MR. VON BOOGIE?

19:17.590 --> 19:20.327
I BELIEVE
IT'S...DR. VON BOOGIE.

19:20.327 --> 19:22.562
[ LAUGHS ]

19:22.562 --> 19:25.398
CAPTAIN SHAKE IT
REPORTING FOR DUTY.

19:25.398 --> 19:26.933
DOCTOR, WHAT TIME IS IT?

19:31.971 --> 19:34.874
IT'S TIME TO GET FUNKY!

19:34.874 --> 19:37.510
[ DISCO MUSIC PLAYS ]

19:48.355 --> 19:51.023
NOW IF I CALL IN SICK,

19:51.023 --> 19:53.226
IT WON'T BE A LIE.
